Package: killsuru
Version: 0.1.0
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Akira Morooka <0825araakimoro@gmail.com>
Installed-Size: 34
Recommends: ncurses-bin
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Homepage: https://github.com/araaki12345/killsuru
Description: Show SUSURUTV ASCII art when you run kill
 killsuru wraps the shell `kill' builtin with a tiny shell function so that
 a SUSURUTV ASCII art is printed whenever a process is successfully signalled.
 .
 The real /bin/kill is never touched: the wrapper is a shell function that
 calls the shell builtin internally, so removing the package fully restores
 the original behaviour. The wrapper is enabled for interactive bash and zsh
 sessions for all users, and never affects non-interactive scripts.
 .
 The displayed art lives in /usr/share/killsuru/art.txt and can be overridden
 per user via ~/.config/killsuru/art.txt.
